The defendant Telly S Hunt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Defendant Telly S Hunt in court with attorney Justin Singleton.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS. 

Statements made as to sentencing.

AMENDED COUNT 1 - CONCURRENT:
Defendant sentenced to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 46 days time served.  Huber privileges for work and/or school.   No electronic monitoring.   COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.

AMENDED COUNT 2 - CONCURRENT:
Defendant sentenced to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 46 days time served.  Huber privileges for work and/or school.   No electronic monitoring.   COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
* Cognitive intervention programming.
* Participate in a Health Relationship program.
* Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
   and successfully complete recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol.
* Random urine screens and breathalyzer test.
* Court order 25 hours of community service at a non-profit organization.
* Obtain High School diploma.
* Obtain and maintain employment and/or school and/or vocational training.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges,
   and supervision fees or CIVIL JUDGMENT will be entered.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
